## index.html.hbs
funding-page-title = Funding
funding-intro = Rust depends on hundreds of contributors who improve it on a daily basis, many of whom are volunteers. We want them to be properly supported to ensure the long-term health of the Rust Project. We are very grateful for any financial contributions that go towards supporting the development of Rust. This page describes several ways how you can support Rust contributors.
funding-rfmf-title = Rust Foundation Maintainer Fund
funding-rfmf-description = The Rust Foundation Maintainer Fund collects donations that are then used to provide stable funding for contributors who maintain critical areas of the Rust toolchain. This program is managed by the <a href="{ $funding-team-url }">Funding team</a>.<br /><br />
    By contributing to this fund, you directly support the development and maintenance of Rust.
funding-rfmf-donate = Donate to the Maintainer Fund
funding-sponsors-title = Sponsor individual contributors
funding-sponsors-description = You can also sponsor specific individuals that work on Rust directly, through their GitHub Sponsors account. You can find such Rust contributors that can be funded below.
